rComments: GREAT PROF!!! BEST CLASSES I HAVE TAKEN AT UOFT(NEW351 AND HIS295). HELPFUL AND VERY KNOWLEDGEABLE

A class with Soske is definately not a bird course, but he is quick to learn student's names, notices when they put in real effort,  is always respectful of questions and accomodates good discussions or relevant sidetracks with his flexible lecture schedule. If you don't want to have your intellectual world shaken, don't take this course.

Taking a class with Jon Soske is  probably one of the most enlightening experiences you'll have in your entire time at U of T. He's articulate, intelligent, and he challenges you to think outside your anglo-american box, which for U of T is highly refreshing. The courses he teaches can be difficult, but extremely rewarding if you   let them be.

Soske's class is no walk through the park..but it is easily one the most beneficial classes offered at UofT. He's very knowledgeable and a great public speaker. The assigned readings really reflect how well he understands his field of study. The material is challenging but Soske goes out of his way to ensure that students understand the theory

Jon Soske was a great professor who gave very insightful lectures. He was also available twice a week during his office hours to explain our readings and help us with our assignments. I attended almost all of the lectures for His 295 and I was overall throughly impressed with the professor's overall knowledge of Africa's history and people.
Jon has "Nerd" written all over him. Very knowledgeable and lives like an intellectual.
